git checkout:-
1. like changing your outfit and clening your room at same time. it does both things!
2. git checkout <branch> is like picking a new outfit(switching tasks).
3. git checkout -b <new-brnach> is like making new outfit and wearing it right away.
4. git checkout <file> is like cleaning up messy room(fixing a file).
5. git checkout <commit-hash> is like looking at an old photo album (going back in time to an older task).
6. like doing two things at once (can change outfits and clean the room).
7. you might accidentally clean something you didn't want to like cleaning your favorite toy!

git switch:-
1. Like only changing your outfit. No room cleaning!
2. git switch <branch> is also like picking a new outfit (switching tasks).
3. git switch -c <new-branch> is like making a new outfit and putting it on.
4. Cannot clean the room (no file dixing allowed here).
5. git switch --detach <commit-hash> is the same as going back in time but no changing things.
6. Only for changing outfits (easy and focused).
7. No risk here, just changing outfits, so no accidents!


